cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the task of pixel-wise semantic segmentation, which is a core problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper compares two popular techniques for this task, Decision Forests (DF) and Neural Networks (NN), and explores the relationship between them. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper applies these techniques to two different applications in computer vision and biology, suggesting that it could also be relevant to the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
